{
  "texts": [
    "Combines RNN to learn representations, DDQN with n-step returns, dueling networks with an additional LSTM layer, Prioritized Distributional ER, and experiences from agents training in parallel.",
    "1 3 Proposes a new hyperparameter for the buffer size and demonstrates that both a small and a large buffer can heavily hurt the learning process.",
    "Remediates the negative influence of a large buffer by adding the current transition to the sampled batch and using the corrected batch to train the agent.",
    "CLEAR (Rolnick et al. 2019) DeepMind Lab tasks",
    "Introduces a method that reduces catastrophic forgetting in multi-task RL by leveraging off-policy learning, behavioral cloning from replay to enhance stability, and on-policy learning to preserve plasticity, which does not require any knowledge of the tasks being learned."
  ]
